1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Welcome to ArtsFolio.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:18,000
In this short tour, you’ll learn how to navigate your admin area,
understand the dashboard, preview your site, and find help.

3
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:30,000
After you sign in, first confirm that you’re working on the correct site.

4
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Your site name appears in the admin sidebar.
This prevents edits from landing in the wrong studio.

5
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:56,000
The sidebar is your main map.

6
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Dashboard returns to the overview.
Content holds About and Contact material.

7
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Artworks, Portfolio Sections, Events, Messages, Sales,
Settings, and Help each lead to a focused workspace.

8
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Think of the dashboard as your control room.

9
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Use it to spot items needing attention,
jump to common tasks, and confirm normal activity.

10
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:12,000
The dashboard gives you the signal.
The detailed page gives you the tools.

11
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Keep your public site close while you work.

12
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:48,000
Edit one area, save it, then inspect the public result,
especially on a phone.

13
00:02:48,000 --> 00:03:05,000
The Onboarding page gathers your setup tools in one place.

14
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:22,000
Use the checklist, guided tour, function index,
and training resources.

15
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Resetting onboarding progress does not delete your site content,
artwork, settings, users, messages, or sales.

16
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Help is available from inside your site.

17
00:03:54,000 --> 00:04:12,000
The function index explains what each admin page does,
when to use it, and what to check before saving.

18
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Written guides can remain open in another tab while you work.

19
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:46,000
Change one group of settings at a time.
Save before leaving the page.

20
00:04:46,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Read validation messages and inspect the relevant public page
on desktop and mobile.

21
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:28,000
Treat your admin area as private workspace.

22
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Invite helpers through Users instead of sharing passwords,
and do not expose customer or visitor information.

23
00:05:46,000 --> 00:06:02,000
The sidebar is your map, the dashboard is your control room,
and the public site is your proof.

24
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:10,000
Next: site identity, branding, and content.
